## 🎯 ADVANCED TECHNIQUE 1 — FEW-SHOT PROMPTING

### What Is It?

Show the AI **1-2 examples of perfect output** BEFORE asking it
to generate the real thing. The AI matches your example quality
instead of guessing what "good" looks like.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ZERO-SHOT (no examples)                               │
│  "Write a commit message for this diff"                │
│  → AI guesses your quality standard                   │
│  → Output varies wildly every time                    │
│                                                         │
│  ONE-SHOT (1 example)                                  │
│  "Here is an example of a perfect commit message:      │
│   feat(api): add Pydantic validation to story endpoint │
│   - Reject invalid age range (must be 3-10)            │
│   - Strip whitespace from child name automatically     │
│   Now write one for THIS diff: [diff]"                 │
│  → AI matches your example exactly                    │
│  → Consistent output every single time                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### When To Use Few-Shot:

```
✅ USE when:
- You need consistent FORMAT every time
- The task has a specific quality bar
- Zero-shot keeps giving wrong structure
- You have a "house style" for output

❌ SKIP when:
- Simple factual questions
- Task is fully defined by format alone
- You genuinely want creative variety
```

